## **Develop the Character** 

The character development process is mostly the same as the existing process for built-in characters. 

The only real difference is that you don’t have to recompile the project and custom logic outside of the blueprint assets is written in Lua instead of C++. 

## **Playtest the Character** 

**IMPORTANT:** In order to playtest your character in the editor, **you must be signed into Steam**, or the editor will crash. 

For now, run the game in the Unreal Engine to playtest. 

There is support for playing your character locally in a build of the game, but a build of the game that supports it has not been added yet. Similarly, we plan on having multiplayer support for testing and using your mod characters as well soon.

* When in game go to one of the local fighting modes like versus or training  
* Select the workshop button in the character select screen UI  
* In your playerslot will popup a list of loaded modded characters, select the character you would like to use  
* If you do not see your character here:  
  * Stop playing in Editor  
  * Go to the character data of your mod   
  * Open up the blueprint to force UE to load it  
    Proceed to the game as usual. 

    #### **FASTER PLAYTEST OPTION** 

    You can also select the character you want by choosing their default skin and color choice in the **Edit \> Editor Preferences \> Rivals Developer Settings**.
